headline: Super Micro Computer Stock Collapse: Is the Worst Over?
summary: Things have gone from bad to worse for Super Micro Computer (NASDAQ: SMCI).  After a scathing short report highlighted questionable accounting practices, the company's auditor resigned, and it has not been able to file its annual report at its expected due date.  As of this writing, Super Micro Computer stock is down 82% from highs set earlier this year, wiping out billions of dollars in shareholder value.
